block.l: Do you know how to swim? (Y or N)
Now I am old enough to swim. I will go swimming in the ocean!
I am not old enough to swim in the ocean by myself!
I don't know how to swim, I will build a sand castle.

scripts.comment: Norman the penguin could go swimming in the coean only if he is older than 7 and knows how to swim. If he is not old enough and does not know how to swim he will build a sand castle.
